Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.57,0:03:04.33,sign_4330_48_Subject_,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H54584a&}Subject:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.57,0:03:04.33,sign_4330_49_1_hour_from_now_,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,1 hour from now, Dobu will \Nshow up at Shibaura Wharf. \NBe a real hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.10,0:03:16.92,Default,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't uploaded any videos recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.93,0:03:21.29,Default,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,You should catch Dobu soon \Nand become a real hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.97,0:03:24.95,Default,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,You know you've been \Ngetting more haters recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.45,0:03:27.45,Default,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,They're saying you're not a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.45,0:03:30.20,Default,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,That you're just an approval-hungry monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.20,0:03:32.69,Default,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,That you're scared of Dobu.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.69,0:03:35.64,Default,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,That you brainwashed them into making \Nofferings, but they've come to their senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.64,0:03:39.16,Default,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,That once you peel back your pretense \Nof divinity, you're just an ordinary guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.16,0:03:41.16,Default,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,That you're just a one-hit wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.16,0:03:43.88,Default,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,That you're sleeping with\N your female followers...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.88,0:03:45.82,Default,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I guess that last one is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.82,0:03:47.67,Default,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,It frustrates me, y'know?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.67,0:03:51.37,Default,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,I can't just tell them \NKabasawa-sama is the real deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.37,0:03:54.00,Default,REINA,0000,0000,0000,,Looking at you lately, \NI realize that you really are—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.00,0:03:55.29,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.29,0:03:57.28,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.28,0:03:59.03,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Society made all this fuss about me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.03,0:04:01.21,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,They thrust this attention \Non me, put me in the line of fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.21,0:04:02.68,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't ask to be deified!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.68,0:04:06.26,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know the kind \Nof pressure I'm under!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.26,0:04:08.26,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so scared, I don't know what to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.26,0:04:10.27,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,This is who your god is!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.27,0:04:12.14,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,This is who your hero is!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.14,0:04:13.54,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Leave, bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.95,0:04:30.95,sign_6449_76_11_7_Sunday,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,11/7 Sunday
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.95,0:04:30.95,sign_6449_77_1_hour_from_now_,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,1 hour from now...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.33,0:04:41.34,sign_6554_78_1_hour_from_now_,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,1 hour from now, Dobu will \Nshow up at Shibaura Wharf.\N Be a real hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.49,0:04:47.81,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,You're treating me like your bodyguard?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.81,0:04:49.72,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,You've really made it, haven't you, Odokawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.72,0:04:51.22,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Still acting like my superior, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.22,0:04:53.88,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.88,0:04:55.88,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Our goals are different,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.88,0:04:59.63,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,but we're partners on the same level, \Nwho are temporarily working together.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.63,0:05:01.72,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,So, where's Kakihana?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.72,0:05:03.64,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Shibaura Wharf.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.64,0:05:06.11,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on. Isn't that—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.11,0:05:09.04,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,The girl Kakihana met through a dating site
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.04,0:05:12.56,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,and the girl who was with \NYamamoto are the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.56,0:05:17.79,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Kakihana went missing at the same time \NYamamoto and his girl headed to the wharf.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.79,0:05:20.66,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,They're probably running a badger game.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.66,0:05:23.53,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,That would make it Yano's job.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.53,0:05:25.64,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do anything about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.64,0:05:28.39,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care about the decorum \Nof your criminal activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.39,0:05:30.42,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I only care about rescuing Kakihana.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.42,0:05:32.46,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,This is gonna be a pain in the ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.46,0:05:34.32,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't Yano your junior?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.32,0:05:37.63,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one obsessed with hierarchies \Nand pledges made over sake cups.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.63,0:05:39.56,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You should be able to \Nresolve this by talking—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.56,0:05:42.04,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't work with Yano.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.04,0:05:45.61,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,There's an unspoken rule that we don't \Ninterfere with each other's business.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.61,0:05:48.11,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,I may not get along with Yano,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.11,0:05:51.83,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,but we're both trying \Nto make money for the boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.16,0:05:57.12,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,If I can't save Kakihana, \NI'm not helping you rob a bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.12,0:06:00.71,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't that mean Yano \Nis interfering with your job?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.71,0:06:03.20,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,You think you're so witty, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.64,0:06:14.56,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Get down!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.56,0:06:17.06,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Shit, it grazed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.36,0:06:26.77,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Park us somewhere. I'm taking back my gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.77,0:06:29.52,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,No way. He's trying to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.52,0:06:31.99,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you didn't care if you died.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.99,0:06:34.02,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no. I don't like pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.02,0:06:35.99,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,He's terrifying. What's his problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.99,0:06:37.55,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Are we still in Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.68,0:07:02.32,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.65,0:07:03.56,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Let's run for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.19,0:07:17.70,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we lost him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.70,0:07:19.45,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you run?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.45,0:07:22.08,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,That was a one-in-a-million chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.08,0:07:25.94,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I can't let you or I die right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.03,0:07:32.80,Default,KAKIHANA,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.80,0:07:34.90,Default,KAKIHANA,0000,0000,0000,,Um, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.90,0:07:37.88,Default,SEKIGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.88,0:07:40.10,Default,SEKIGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,You got a tiny bladder, or what? Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.79,0:07:43.40,Default,SEKIGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,This is just like the problem \Nof keeping death row inmates
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.40,0:07:46.20,Default,SEKIGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,who aren't assigned \Nto penal labor incarcerated.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.20,0:07:49.07,Default,SEKIGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta take care of 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.35,0:08:00.58,Default,SEKIGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm leaving, so you'd better get it all out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.00,0:08:03.04,Default,SEKIGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll come back to check \Non you in about three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.25,0:08:10.29,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you scared of water?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.29,0:08:14.36,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows? Maybe \NI drowned in a previous life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.36,0:08:17.72,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Well, phobias don't always have a reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.64,0:08:23.58,Default,SEKIGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure Yano-san will find a way \Nto turn your life into money.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.58,0:08:25.65,Default,SEKIGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,A way to use—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.98,0:08:29.12,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.12,0:08:39.64,Default,SEKIGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if it isn't Dobu-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.64,0:08:40.90,Default,SEKIGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.90,0:08:42.68,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Sekiguchi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.68,0:08:45.73,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here to rescue a kidnapping victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.73,0:08:48.21,Default,SEKIGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,What did Yano-san have to say about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.21,0:08:50.28,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't talked to Yano.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.73,0:08:52.71,Default,SEKIGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Then please leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.71,0:08:55.13,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,It's cold out here. At least let me inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.13,0:08:56.76,Default,SEKIGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.76,0:08:58.51,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,A taxi driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.93,0:09:01.01,Default,SEKIGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,You made a man with \Nan honest job your underling?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.01,0:09:02.31,Default,SEKIGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,You've fallen far, Dobu.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.31,0:09:05.64,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,And you're out runnin' badger games, \Nso I could say the same of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.27,0:09:10.33,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, taxi driver. I'm gonna \Nchuck this guy into the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.33,0:09:12.53,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Take Kakihana and get outta\N here in the meantime.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.33,0:09:56.07,Default,KAKIHANA,0000,0000,0000,,Odokawa...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.35,0:09:58.73,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to keep you waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.99,0:10:08.19,Default,KAKIHANA,0000,0000,0000,,What are they doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.19,0:10:10.04,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,They're idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.81,0:10:13.68,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,They're idiots, so they don't know how \Nto express their feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.68,0:10:17.97,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,They use duty and human nature \Nas an excuse for violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.57,0:10:21.51,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's what you'd expect \Nfrom living creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.40,0:10:37.50,Default,KAKIHANA,0000,0000,0000,,I get to go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.50,0:10:40.56,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, let's go home. You must've been cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.50,0:10:53.88,Default,SEKIGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute, Dobu-san. \NI let Kakihana escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.88,0:10:58.02,Default,SEKIGUCHI,0000,0000,0000,,If you beat me, then I won't \Nbe able to face Yano-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.02,0:10:59.43,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Not my problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.43,0:11:01.69,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,It's your fault that you couldn't beat me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.69,0:11:05.54,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you take this opportunity to quit\N doing low-tier jobs like badger games?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.52,0:11:11.06,Default,KAKIHANA,0000,0000,0000,,Odokawa, I don't know what to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.06,0:11:13.36,Default,KAKIHANA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.04,0:11:26.73,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! Skull mask...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.46,0:11:29.94,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were an amateur.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.94,0:11:30.96,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.67,0:11:43.03,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Remember how we went to Hakone \Nfor off-campus education in high school?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.03,0:11:44.47,Default,KAKIHANA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we sure did.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.47,0:11:48.14,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You bought a yosegi puzzle box \Nas a souvenir, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.14,0:11:49.78,Default,KAKIHANA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.78,0:11:52.01,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,One with 36 steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.01,0:11:55.07,Default,KAKIHANA,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right? I'm surprised you remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.07,0:11:58.29,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You kept it in your bag for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.29,0:12:00.98,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You'd perform all 36 steps and \Nopen the thing, like a showoff.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.98,0:12:03.94,Default,KAKIHANA,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like I remember that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.94,0:12:06.24,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember what happened to that box?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.24,0:12:07.49,Default,KAKIHANA,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.49,0:12:08.98,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You put your family's stamp inside it
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.98,0:12:11.62,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,and left it on top of the shoe \Ncupboard in your entryway.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.09,0:12:16.70,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,When a delivery arrived, your mom tried \Nto open it through trial-and-error.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.70,0:12:19.17,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,The deliveryman watched her the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.05,0:12:26.01,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Ultimately, she smashed it open \Nand got the stamp out, like an otter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.01,0:12:28.31,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You got in a lot of trouble later.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.31,0:12:30.99,Default,KAKIHANA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's what happened. What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.99,0:12:32.66,Default,KAKIHANA,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say, here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.66,0:12:35.11,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You've been pathetic ever since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.53,0:12:49.11,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I did it. I finally did it, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.11,0:12:51.24,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I got Dobu. Me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.24,0:12:52.29,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Dobu!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.29,0:12:54.56,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Kabasawa. Give it up, you punk!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.56,0:12:55.87,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Apologize, you bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.87,0:12:58.17,Italics,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Apologize to everyone in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.17,0:13:02.21,Italics,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, haters. And you shitheads who did \Nnothing but heckle me from safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.21,0:13:03.65,Italics,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You all talked a lotta shit about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.65,0:13:05.05,Italics,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Well, who's the punk now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.05,0:13:07.24,Italics,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, I got Dobu all by myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.24,0:13:09.43,Italics,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the only charismatic leader you need!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.43,0:13:12.11,Italics,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You're all my slaves!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.18,0:13:14.00,Italics,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.74,0:13:18.42,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,You have a gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.31,0:13:28.75,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.44,0:13:34.81,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Then let's \Nhear what you have to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.81,0:13:36.55,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Or would you rather duke it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.97,0:13:38.00,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I s-surrender!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.00,0:13:39.17,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.86,0:13:43.66,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see, I can't beat you in a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.66,0:13:46.66,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Is that the extent of your sense of justice?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.66,0:13:50.99,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,You vowed to catch me, \Nwhen your resolve was this weak?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.25,0:13:55.13,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,You never had any sense of justice \Nor resolve to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.13,0:13:58.47,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you try reflecting on\N the principles that drove you to act?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.43,0:14:01.19,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.19,0:14:05.75,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,You got it. Now, why not dig a little deeper?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.75,0:14:07.82,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why{\i0} did you want attention?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.34,0:14:10.00,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.00,0:14:12.36,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,It's because you wanted approval \Nfrom others, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.36,0:14:15.06,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,And why did you want approval from others?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.06,0:14:17.63,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Because you have no self-esteem.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.63,0:14:21.04,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Because you have no confidence, \Nyou can't approve of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.04,0:14:23.50,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,But despite that, you're more \Nnarcissistic than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.50,0:14:26.01,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,No! I'm not a narcissist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.01,0:14:28.63,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I hated who I was before I had attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.63,0:14:33.68,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,That said, receiving attention didn't \Nmagically make me like myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.68,0:14:36.86,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,But it felt so good, so I kept escalating.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.86,0:14:39.11,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Now I'm so scared, I don't know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.11,0:14:41.84,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I regret it. I've always hated myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.84,0:14:43.83,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I despise who I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.83,0:14:47.80,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I've always wanted to disappear. \NI've always wanted to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.80,0:14:54.48,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saying your extreme rejection of\N and hatred for yourself {\i1}is{\i0} narcissism.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.48,0:14:57.19,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Normal people aren't that\N interested in themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.19,0:14:59.62,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.19,0:15:03.93,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Find a mentor you trust, not an \Nunspecified large number of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.93,0:15:06.31,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,One you can respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.31,0:15:08.41,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,If you've got a baseline to measure \Nyourself from, you won't waver.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.41,0:15:10.85,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,If that's too difficult, \Nthen approve of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.85,0:15:13.99,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, you need \Nto learn to accept yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.92,0:15:15.93,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.93,0:15:19.36,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate your words, \NDobu-san. I hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.36,0:15:22.37,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, I, Taichi Kabasawa, \Nshall return to university,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.37,0:15:27.16,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,resume looking for a job, \Nand live my life one day at a time!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.16,0:15:29.59,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Because of you, my eyes have been opened.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.59,0:15:30.85,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.85,0:15:31.75,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.75,0:15:35.87,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait. I'm not running \Na self-improvement seminar here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.29,0:15:39.60,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,As you know, I don't make an honest living.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.60,0:15:44.08,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,I need you to compensate me \Nfor all the harm you've caused me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.08,0:15:45.38,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.38,0:15:47.63,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,And what can you give me, if not your life?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.43,0:15:52.07,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,U-Um, I bought an a-apartment. \NYou can have that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.07,0:15:54.60,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,A-And a car. I drove it here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.60,0:15:57.60,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I have some money left, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.60,0:16:00.48,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Please... Please forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.48,0:16:03.62,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's the wisest choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.62,0:16:05.98,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,You did make that money off me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.98,0:16:09.11,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,So... Will you forgive me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.11,0:16:09.67,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.67,0:16:11.11,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.11,0:16:13.33,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You're a good person, Dobu-san—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.33,0:16:14.43,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,One more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.95,0:16:17.95,sign_15631_176_Goriki_Clinic,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Goriki Clinic
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.86,0:16:22.41,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,He's such an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.67,0:16:25.12,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,His mind and body are\N in a pretty weakened state.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.12,0:16:27.48,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,He'll have to stay here for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.48,0:16:29.01,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't have any money.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.01,0:16:31.09,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give him a discount.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.64,0:16:35.12,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Odokawa. What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.31,0:16:39.27,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you go with Dobu to save Kakihana?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.27,0:16:41.38,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to take down Dobu.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.38,0:16:46.11,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll use whatever I can, and ultimately, \NI'll take out his whole organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.11,0:16:49.76,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,You're just a taxi driver. \NWhy do you need to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.76,0:16:51.15,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do anything dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.83,0:16:53.79,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Are you avenging Shirakawa-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.79,0:16:56.31,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,She's a good girl at heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.31,0:16:58.88,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Dobu got his claws in her \Nbefore she knew any better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.88,0:17:01.09,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,He used her. She's a victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.09,0:17:03.60,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,But in some ways, she brought it on herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.92,0:17:06.33,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,She may have been controlled by fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.33,0:17:09.75,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,but it was her weakness that \Nmade her follow Dobu's instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.75,0:17:12.49,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,She must've had plenty \Nof chances to leave him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.49,0:17:15.47,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Shirakawa-san threw those chances away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.92,0:17:17.88,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't bring it on herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.88,0:17:21.68,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you a doctor? Have you \Nheard of Stockholm Syndrome?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.68,0:17:27.09,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,It's when kidnapping victims develop \Naffection for their kidnappers, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.09,0:17:32.00,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Following Dobu's instructions \Nwas her strategy for survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.00,0:17:34.33,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,She felt that cornered.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.33,0:17:37.35,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,She was controlled by violence and threats.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.35,0:17:38.99,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,It was an unfair situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.99,0:17:43.66,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,But that's no reason for you \Nto cross this dangerous bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.66,0:17:45.66,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Do you love Shirakawa-san that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.38,0:17:51.88,sign_25664_293_Taichi_Kabasawa_,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Taichi Kabasawa-san has uploaded a video.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.42,0:18:45.85,sign_28196_336__Declaration_of_,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,[Shutting Down] Taichi Kabasawa Defeated [Surrender]
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.84,0:17:57.65,Italics,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,To everyone watching the \NKabasawa channel, as of this day,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.65,0:18:05.38,Italics,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I, Taichi Kabasawa, have decided to stop \Nuploading videos and holding online salons.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.38,0:18:10.35,Italics,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,All Kabasawa accounts will be \Nerased in a few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.35,0:18:15.13,Italics,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I am not a hero, nor champion of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.13,0:18:20.17,Italics,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for ultimately \Ndeceiving all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.17,0:18:27.43,Italics,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Dobu—Dobu-san has nothing to do \Nwith this, so don't get the wrong idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.43,0:18:29.72,Italics,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I simply lost to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.72,0:18:34.94,Italics,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,So I ask that the rest of you \Nleave Dobu-san alone, also.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.94,0:18:41.83,Italics,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Also, um, I'm not offering refunds \Nfor the online salon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.83,0:18:44.38,Italics,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate your understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.56,0:18:48.32,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,He's a tough guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.32,0:18:51.58,Default,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Both Sekiguchi and Kabasawa lost to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.05,0:18:54.68,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Did you post it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.68,0:18:56.41,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.50,0:19:02.62,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.96,0:19:08.26,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing. I'm just grateful that \NI made it through this unscathed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.26,0:19:09.85,Default,KABASAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.85,0:19:12.42,Default,DOBU,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'll be taking your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.52,0:19:18.86,Default,MAN A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you'll fall if you \Ndon't quit messing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.86,0:19:20.63,Default,KANON,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.89,0:20:04.39,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,Odokawa-kun, are you home?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.39,0:20:07.22,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,His car's not here. I don't think he's home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.83,0:20:10.93,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Well, that's a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.93,0:20:13.56,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm the landlord here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.56,0:20:15.41,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.41,0:20:19.86,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,I hadn't introduced myself yet. \NI'm Odokawa's friend, Goriki.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.17,0:20:23.99,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,What's the problem? Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.63,0:20:25.92,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, all sorts of things lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.92,0:20:30.57,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,First the police showed up, \Nthen his window was broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.57,0:20:35.77,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,Odokawa-kun said he was going to move \Nbecause he didn't want to cause trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.77,0:20:38.35,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,How is that a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.35,0:20:39.71,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,It's a huge problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.71,0:20:41.98,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Odokawa-kun's guardian,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.98,0:20:45.55,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,and I've already received enough rent \Nfor him to live here for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.55,0:20:47.14,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,From the foundation?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.14,0:20:47.98,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.98,0:20:52.89,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,But since Odokawa-kun started working, \Nhe's been paying more than his rent.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.89,0:20:55.89,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,He told me to return the money \Nto the foundation's representative.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.89,0:20:59.14,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,How long has Odokawa been living here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.14,0:21:00.98,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,Since fifth grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.98,0:21:05.28,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Alone? He's been living off \Nthe foundation's money?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.28,0:21:08.73,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Sometimes he'd eat at my place,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.73,0:21:10.66,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,but for the most part, he'd refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.66,0:21:12.68,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,He said he didn't want to trouble me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.68,0:21:15.93,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,I helped him with any necessary business \Nat school and the public office.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.93,0:21:17.79,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,I just felt so bad for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.79,0:21:22.71,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Could you tell me the name of that \Nrepresentative or the foundation itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.71,0:21:24.68,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.68,0:21:28.57,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,Their condition is that in exchange \Nfor not seeking any profit or tax benefits,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.57,0:21:31.78,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,our identities are kept secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.78,0:21:35.32,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,But you deposit the money you get \Nfrom Odokawa, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.32,0:21:36.46,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.46,0:21:39.94,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,You think I'd steal it? How dreadful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.94,0:21:42.14,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.14,0:21:44.48,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,If Odokawa-kun is moving,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.48,0:21:47.24,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,then I intend to return the money \NI've been holding onto.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.05,0:21:51.53,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know where Odokawa lived \Nbefore coming here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.36,0:21:56.54,Default,LANDLORD,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was Shiroku in Chichibu.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.54,0:21:58.40,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroku in Chichibu.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.40,0:22:00.95,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, he lived alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.95,0:22:04.62,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Was living at an orphanage \Nor with family not an option?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.62,0:22:07.64,Default,LANDLADY,0000,0000,0000,,It's what Odokawa-kun wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.64,0:22:12.28,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,I guess so. His parents \Nmight return someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.28,0:22:14.14,Default,LANDLADY,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.14,0:22:16.68,Default,LANDLADY,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really his friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.68,0:22:20.07,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,I heard Odokawa's parents are missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.07,0:22:22.10,Default,LANDLADY,0000,0000,0000,,Odokawa-kun told you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.10,0:22:23.54,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,It's what I was told.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.54,0:22:25.78,Default,LANDLADY,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe that's what he believes...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.78,0:22:27.37,Default,GORIKI,0000,0000,0000,,They're not missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.26,0:22:31.24,Default,LANDLADY,0000,0000,0000,,They're dead. Both of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.97,0:23:50.44,Next_Time,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Next Time: {\fs22\b1}We Have No Tomorrow{\fs\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.62,0:23:36.51,Italics,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Capoeira.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.51,0:23:37.60,Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Uh, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.60,0:23:40.46,Italics,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You said before that you didn't know\N how people pick up capoeira.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.46,0:23:42.47,Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Oh, yeah. Did I?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.47,0:23:45.52,Italics,SHIRAKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Do you want me to hit you \Nwith a cabeçada into an aú batido?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.52,0:23:48.64,Italics,ODOKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Sorry, sorry. I don't know what those \Ntechniques are, but they sound scary.